HEADWORD: Arillus
<hw>A*ril"lus</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From LL. <ets>arilli</ets> dry
grapes, perh. fr. L. <ets>aridus</ets> dry: cf. F,.
<ets>arille</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A exterior covering,
forming a false coat or appendage to a seed, as the loose, transparent
bag inclosing the seed of the white water lily. The mace of the nutmeg
is also an <xex>aril</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

